    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Popular name for a type of 18th-century American dressing table with drawers, set on high legs, and similar in form to the lower section of a high chest of drawers, which it was often made to match.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Nombre popular para un tipo de tocador americano del siglo XVIII con cajones, colocado sobre patas altas, y parecido en forma a la sección inferior de una cómoda alta, la que a menudo era fabricada en conjunto.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
